  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I would say that on infinite like interfaces you should not try to sync the url with the current \"page\" (= scroll position). Twitter does not do it for instance and I think that's the right move here.\r\n\r\nIf you want bookmakable pages then use the load more button but without having an infinite scroll example, replace the results everytime.\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?",
